Updated dynatable to allow for unknown browser caching implementations.

Apparently there is a bug in Firefox 7 where their pushState limit is
between 291,274 and 292,944 characters for the stringified JSON cache
object, even though their documentation still says it's 640,000.
Furthermore, each browser can change this limit in about:config under
the browser.history.maxStateObjectSize setting (even though FF7 doesn't
seem to properly obey this).

As a result, dynatable's state caching needs to allow for unknown
strigify implementations and caching limits. The only real way to do
this is putting the caching code inside a try..catch block.

Updated dynatable to account for Mozilla's 640k imposed limit on
pushState data. Also fixed perPage select to update from pushState pop.
